emoved stub tag", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gary_Waldhorn"}
{"title_page": "Be Prepared (song)", "text_new": "{{distinguish|text=the song of the same name by Tom Lehrer, see ''[[Songs by Tom Lehrer]]''}}\n{{more citations needed|date=April 2008}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name     = Be Prepared\n| cover    =\n| alt      =\n| type     =\n| artist   = [[Jeremy Irons]] with [[Whoopi Goldberg]], [[Cheech Marin]] and [[Jim Cummings]]\n| album    = [[The Lion King (1994 soundtrack)|The Lion King]]\n| released = 1994\n| format   =\n| recorded = 1993\n| studio   =\n| venue    =\n| genre    =\n| length   =\n| label    = [[Walt Disney Records|Walt Disney]]\n| writer   = [[Tim Rice]], [[Elton John]]\n| producer =\n}}\n[[Image:ScarAndHyenas.jpg|250px|thumb|right|Scar towers over the hyenas.]]\n\"'''Be Prepared'''\" is a song written by [[Elton John]] and [[Tim Rice]] (music and lyrics, respectively) for the [[Walt Disney Animation Studios|Disney]] animated feature film ''[[The Lion King]]'' (1994). The song was originally performed in the film by [[Jeremy Irons]], with [[Whoopi Goldberg]], [[Cheech Marin]], and [[Jim Cummings]] providing supporting vocals; Cummings performed partial material for [[Scar (The Lion King)|Scar]] after Irons' voice gave out.\n\nThe song is also featured in the 1997 [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] musical ''[[The Lion King]]'', with [[John Vickery (actor)|John Vickery]], [[Kevin Cahoon]], [[Stanley Wayne Mathis]], and [[Tracy Nicole Chapman]] performing it in the original Broadway cast for the musical. [[Chiwetel Ejiofor]] performed an altered version of the song in the 2019 [[The Lion King (2019 film)|film adaptation]].\n\n==''The Lion King''==\nThe song is performed as a musical number by [[Scar (The Lion King)|Scar]], who lusts for the position as king of the Pride Lands. Scar is inspired to develop a plot for both his brother Mufasa and his nephew Simba to be murdered, and tells about this plan through song to a large army of [[spotted hyena]] minions by his pledge to spare the hungry animals from starvation if they provide him with assistance.\n\n====Production====\nOriginally, the song (first called \"Thanks to Me\") was about Scar introducing the hyenas to the lionesses after he pronounced himself king. This idea was eventually scrapped and replaced with ''Be Prepared''.{{citation needed|date=August 2019}} A reprise of the song after Mufasa's death was also cut from the film, but is featured in the [[The Lion King (musical)|musical version]].{{citation needed|date=August 2019}}\n\nIn the beginning of the second verse, an army of hyenas is shown [[Goose step|goose-stepping]] in front of Scar, who is perched on an overlooking cliff in resemblance of [[Adolf Hitler]] with upwards of 22 beams of light pointing straight-up (resembling the [[Cathedral of light]] featured in many of the [[Nuremberg Rallies]]). Shadows cast onto the cliff evoke for a brief second monumental columns. This is modeled after footage from the [[Leni Riefenstahl]]'s [[Nazi Germany|Nazi]] propaganda movie ''[[Triumph of the Will]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/the-lion-king-be-prepared-nazi-film-2014-6|title=The Darkest Song From 'The Lion King' Was Based On A 1935 Nazi Propaganda Film|last=Pallotta|first=Frank|website=Business Insider|access-date=2019-01-29}}</ref>\n\nThough [[Jeremy Irons]] is credited for performing the lead vocals on the song, at the 2012 [[Calgary Comic and Entertainment Expo]], [[Jim Cummings]], who also played Ed, stated that he sang most of the song, and that Irons only did some of the talking.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jim Cummings on Hakuna Matata and Be Prepared|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Wmrdn9eFTK8&t=3m15s|date=3 May 2012}}</ref> However, footage from the film's recording sessions available on the film's 2017 Blu-ray release reveals that Irons sang the entire first verse of the song, while a cursory analysis of the recording suggests (due to a subtle but evident shift in vocal timbre heard in Scar's lead vocal) that Cummings only sang the final verse (\"So be prepared for the coup of the century...\") in the final cut of the film. Cummings has also confirmed this in other interviews, claiming that he sang this last verse due to Irons developing vocal problems during the recording session.<ref>https://www.huffingtonpost.com/jim-hill/lion-king-voice-actors_b_968140.html</ref>\n\n====Original recording====\nOn the original soundtrack recording, Scar opens the song with a [[soliloquy]]:\n\n{{cquote|I never thought hyenas essential. They're crude and unspeakably plain. But maybe they've a glimmer of potential if allied to my vision and brain.}}\n\nIn the film, this is cut and the song begins immediately. This was due to a plot adjustment.<ref>[http://www.lionking.org/scripts/Script.html#prepared TLK Script (HTML 3.0 Version)<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> The soliloquy had Scar considering using the hyenas for his plot, but in the final version of the story he had already used the hyenas in his plans before the song. The soliloquy is, however, included in the Broadway version.{{citation needed|date=August 2019}}\n\n===International versions===\nWhen the movie was first released in 1994, it numbered complexively 28 versions worldwide, including a special [[Zulu language|Zulu]] version made in [[South Africa]]. This is not just the only Zulu dubbing ever made by Disney, but also the only dubbing made in any [[Languages of Africa|African language]], other than [[Arabic]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://disneyinternationaldubbings.weebly.com/the-lion-king--zulu-cast.html|title=The Lion King / Zulu cast|website=Charguigou|access-date=2016-08-24}}</ref> Over the years, the number of dubbings has increased to 41 official versions, to which some unofficial versions have been added by local TV stations and studios in their local languages: namely [[Abaza language|Abaza]], [[Albanian language|Albanian]], [[Arabic]] (TV version), [[Armenian language|Armenian]], [[Austrian German]], [[Crimean Tatar language|Crimean Tatar]], [[Kabardian language|Kabardian]], [[Karachay-Balkar language|Karachay-Balkar]], [[Nogai language|Nogai]], [[Persian language|Persian]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://disneyinternationalvoices.weebly.com/scar.html|title=Scar|website=Charguigou|access-date=2019-06-12}}</ref>\n{{legend|Azure|Highlighted versions were released later than 1994}}\n{| class=\"wikitable collapsible collapsed\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"4\" |\"Be prepared\" worldwide\n|-\n! align=\"left\" |Language\n! align=\"left\" |Performer<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://disneyinternationalvoices.weebly.com/scar.html|title=Scar|website=Charguigou|access-date=2019-06-12}}</ref>\n! align=\"left\" |Title\n! align=\"left\" |Translation\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Arabic language|Arabic]]\n| align=\"left\" |{{illm|\u0639\u0628\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0631\u062d\u0645\u0646 \u0623\u0628\u0648 \u0632\u0647\u0631\u0629 (Abdul Rahman Abu Zahra)|ar|3=\u0639\u0628\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0631\u062d\u0645\u0646 \u0623\u0628\u0648 \u0632\u0647\u0631\u0629}}\n| align=\"left\" |\"\u0627\u0633\u062a\u0639\u062f\u0648\u0627\" (\"Astaeduu\")\n| align=\"left\" |\"Get ready\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:Azure\" |[[Bulgarian language|Bulgarian]]\n| style=\"background:Azure\" |{{illm|\u041d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0430\u0439 \u0423\u0440\u0443\u043c\u043e\u0432 (Nikolay Urumov)|bg|3=\u041d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0430\u0439 \u0423\u0440\u0443\u043c\u043e\u0432}}\n| style=\"background:Azure\" |\"\u0427\u0430\u043a\u0430\u0439 \u0437\u043d\u0430\u043a\" (\"Chakay znak\")\n| style=\"background:Azure\" |\"Wait for a sign\"\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Cantonese]]\n| align=\"left\" |{{illm|\u76e7\u570b\u96c4 (Lo Kwok Hung)|zh|3=\u76e7\u570b\u96c4}}\n| align=\"left\" |\"\u9810\u5099\u597d\" (\"Jyu bei hou\")\n| align=\"left\" |\"Ready\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:Azure\" |[[Croatian language|Croatian]]\n| style=\"background:Azure\" |{{illm|Sini\u0161a Popovi\u0107|hr|3=Sini\u0161a Popovi\u0107}} \n| style=\"background:Azure\" |\"Budi jak\"\n| style=\"background:Azure\" |\"Be strong\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Czech language|Czech]]\n|[[Ji\u0159\u00ed Schmitzer]] <sub>1994</sub>\n| rowspan=\"2\" |\"Bu\u010f p\u0159ipraven\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" |\"Be ready\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:Azure\" |[[Pavel Soukup]] <sub>2003</sub>\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Danish language|Danish]]\n| align=\"left\" |{{Interlanguage link multi|Stig Hoffmeyer|da|3=Stig Hoffmeyer}}\n| align=\"left\" |\"G\u00f8r jer klar\"\n| align=\"left\" |\"Be ready\"\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Dutch language|Dutch]]\n| align=\"left\" |{{Interlanguage link multi|Arnold Gelderman|nl|3=Arnold Gelderman}} \n| align=\"left\" |\"Sta paraat\"\n| align=\"left\" |\"Be prepared\"\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[English language|English]]\n| align=\"left\" |[[Jeremy Irons]] & [[Jim Cummings]]\n| colspan=\"2\" |\"Be prepared\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:Azure\" |[[Estonian language|Estonian]]\n| style=\"background:Azure\" |{{illm|Lauri Saatpalu|et|3=Lauri Saatpalu}} \n| style=\"background:Azure\" |\"K\u00fcll siis n\u00e4ed\"\n| style=\"background:Azure\" |\"Then you see\"\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Finnish language|Finnish]]\n| align=\"left\" |{{Interlanguage link multi|Jukka-Pekka Palo|fi|3=Jukka-Pekka Palo}} \n| align=\"left\" |\"Vallan saan\"\n| align=\"left\" |\"I'll have the power\"\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[French language|French]]\n| align=\"left\" |[[Jean Piat]]\n| align=\"left\" |\"Soyez pr\u00eates\"\n| align=\"left\" |\"Be ready\"\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[German language|German]]\n| align=\"left\" |[[Thomas Fritsch]]\n| align=\"left\" |\"Seid bereit\"\n| align=\"left\" |\"Be ready\"\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Greek language|Greek]]\n| align=\"left\" |\u0391\u03bb\u03ad\u03be\u03b1\u03bd\u03b4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c2 \u03a3\u03c4\u03b1\u03c5\u03c1\u03ac\u03ba\u03b7\u03c2 (Al\u00e9xandros Stavr\u00e1kis)\n| align=\"left\" |\"\u03a5\u03c0'\u03b1\u03c4\u03bc\u03cc\u03bd\" (\"Yp'atm\u00f3n\")\n| align=\"left\" |\"Ready to begin\"\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Hebrew language|Hebrew]]\n| align=\"left\" 